oreign birth being deported and even executed for political activities—Italian anarchism was successfully transplanted. Transnationalism made it more difficult for states to destroy groups spread across wide geographical spaces. In Italy and abroad the strong anarchist identity informed by class, ethnicity, and gender reinforced movement values, promoted movement expansion, and assisted mobilization during times of crisis. In Transnational Radicals, Tomchuk makes use of Italian government security files and Italian-language anarchist newspapers to reconstruct a vibrant and little-studied political movement during a tumultuous period of modern North American history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnarchismxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aAnarchismxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aAnarchismzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aAnarchismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAnarchistsxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aAnarchistsxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aAnarchistszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aAnarchistszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aItaliansxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aItaliansxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aItalianszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aItalianszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTransnationalismxHistoryx20th centuryxCanadaxUnited StatesxHistory. 0aTransnationalismxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Anarchism.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAnarchism in Italy, Canada, United States.  aAnarchism.  aCanadian History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755484140uhttps://www.degruyte